anstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   MQing high value items</span><hr size=1> I haven't ruled out MQing parts of my epic at this early stage (will need to do some serious saving up!), but I'm interested to know how do you protect yourself against a high value MQ item trade?<br>
<br>
I've seen various items go for 50k+, but how is this transaction typically carried out?  <br>
<br>
Do sellers want the cash up front?<br>
Do the buyers only pay up once an item has successfully been handed in? (what happens if previous MQ was only partial and it messes your one up?)<br>
<br>
I guess with the new UI you can see the link to the item the seller should have (can this be hacked?)<br>
<br>
Interested to know peoples experience.<br>
<br>
Canelin<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
