<br>
One way the seller could be dishonest is to have a friend that has the item...that friends sends them the link...they open the link and create their own link and send it to you.  Also, they could just hang out in the Bazaar and see the item there and create a link to send to you.  <br>
<br>
I have heard of MQ having wonderful results and of having horrible results.  My friend MQ'd...(tried to MQ) J-Boots.  The person that he purchased the MQ from had the Ring from the AC as well as the rapier.  My friend had the gold pieces.  The person with the Ring and rapier said she had handed them to Hasten Bootstrutter...but she didn't....she waited for my friend to then hand the gold pieces and she turned in the Ring and the rapier and received the J-Boots...then went LD.  A few days later she was back on and my friend asked her wft was going on.  She stated that she had a lag spike while handing Hasten the items...then she went LD...and when she finally signed back in...she had the J-Boots.  To this day, the situation has never been resolved...and that was just J-Boots....I would be incredibly angry if someone did that to me with my Epic....<br>
<br>
Caveat Emptor....<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
Moon <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193326">Moon's Magelo Profile</A> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1193<br> <font color=#333333>(9/17/02 8:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1068.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MQing high value items</span><hr size=1> That is what frightens me about all those people offering MQ of the Quillmane cloak for 5k.  They could easily say &quot;ok, I turned in the cloak&quot; and wait for you to turn in your items.  Then they turn in the cloak and get the element of wind which they keep for a guildmate and you never see them again.  You just lost your PoA crown now.<br>
<br>
I'd never risk that crown to a person I didn't know.<br>
<br>
The earth staff on the other hand, I'd pay 50k for MQ in a heartbeat.  The other 3 items to turn in are pretty trivial to get compared to that piece.<br>
