<br>
Back then, the seller and I didn't know one another, so we weren't able to trust each other - she wanted all of the money up front.  I felt that the fairest thing to do was to pay her half of the cash up front, and the other half when the MQ was done.  That way, before the MQ, I am putting 8K on the line.  After the MQ, the seller is putting 8K on the line.  There's no secure way to buy an MQ, so I thought that it would be fairest if we both took equal risk.  It took her many hours to figure that one out though..<br>
<br>
In the end, I paid 10K up front and 6K when the job was done (I wanted that staff badly, and didn't want to make any further negotiations).  Luckily, she followed through with it and so did I. <p>[60 Arch Mage] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753" target="_blank">Sage Rascarcapac</a> < Grey Council > <BR>
